CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1945, pg. 2, reads: "Seeking Recruits - Mrs. Mary Cheney, connected with the Eastern Area of the American Red Cross, is here seeking recruits for staff assistants to serve in overseas Red Cross clubs. Mrs. Cheney may be contacted at the Wabash Station on Liberty Avenue. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mary Cheney wearing Red Cross uniform seated at microphone
